## Part C — Design system (ZK theme)

### C.1 Canonical tokens (Tailwind)

Defined in [`tailwind.config.js`](tailwind.config.js). **Prefer these over legacy `brand-*` for new and touched UI:**

| Token                           | Role                                                                                  |
| ------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `zk-base` `#0E0E12`             | Default page background, deepest layer                                                |
| `zk-surface` `#13131A`          | Panels, secondary surfaces                                                            |
| `zk-elevated` `#1A1A22`         | Cards, inputs, raised chips                                                           |
| `zk-violet` `#18141F`           | Subtle violet undertone sections (sparingly)                                          |
| `zk-border`                     | Hairline borders / dividers (violet-tinted)                                           |
| `zk-text` `#E4E4E7`             | Primary text on dark                                                                  |
| `zk-muted` `#9CA3AF`            | Secondary labels, helper text                                                         |
| `zk-indigo` / `zk-indigo-hover` | **Primary** interactive accent (buttons, key links)                                   |
| `zk-indigo-glow`                | Soft outer glow on **primary** CTAs only (use rarely)                                 |
| `zk-cyan`                       | **Security / encryption / tech** indicators, code accents, “verified” line highlights |
| `zk-safe` `#5DAE8C`             | **Encrypted / safe / success** state only (muted green—never neon)                    |

**Legacy `brand-*` tokens:** still used across the app. During redesign, **migrate touched files** toward `zk-*` where practical. Do not bulk-replace the entire repo in one PR unless the task says “full migration.”

### C.2 Typography

- **UI sans:** `font-zk-sans` (Inter stack). Use for all in-app UI text when touching a file for redesign.
- **Code / keys / IDs:** `font-zk-mono` (JetBrains Mono stack). Use for API key previews, env snippets, search tokens, timestamps, badge labels that mimic CLI.

**Scale (Tailwind, adjust per context but stay in this system):**

| Use              | Classes (indicative)                                                                              |
| ---------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Page title       | `text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-[-0.03em] text-zk-text`                              |
| Section title    | `text-lg md:text-xl font-semibold tracking-[-0.02em] text-zk-text`                                |
| Body             | `text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed text-zk-text`                                               |
| Secondary / help | `text-xs md:text-sm text-zk-muted`                                                                |
| Overline / label | `font-zk-mono text-[10px] md:text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-zk-cyan/80` or `text-zk-muted` |

**Rules:**

- Headlines: **tight tracking** (`tracking-[-0.03em]` to `[-0.045em]`), **no** decorative display fonts.
- Avoid all-caps sentences except **micro labels** (e.g. status chips).
- **Never** mix more than two font contexts in one component (sans + mono only).

### C.3 Layout & density

- **Philosophy:** “Dense but calm” (Linear / developer-tooling). Prefer readable `max-w-*` on text columns; tables and dashboards can be full width.
- **Page padding:** `px-4 md:px-6 lg:px-8` for main content; align with marketing sections unless layout constraints (e.g. sidebar) dictate otherwise.
- **Vertical rhythm:** section gaps `gap-6` to `gap-10`; avoid excessive `py-24`-style whitespace inside dense tools **unless** it is a marketing-like empty state.
- **Sidebar / shell:** keep **one** clear hierarchy: base → surface → elevated. Sidebar should feel like a **slightly different elevation** from main (`zk-surface` / `zk-elevated`), not a unrelated color (avoid random gradients unless matching a defined pattern below).

### C.4 Radius, border, shadow

- **Cards / modals:** `rounded-xl` (12px) default; `rounded-2xl` for hero-style panels only.
- **Buttons / chips:** `rounded-full` for primary/secondary pills; `rounded-md` or `rounded-lg` for compact controls.
- **Borders:** default `border border-zk-border`. On **primary** focus for emphasis: `border-zk-indigo/40` with **very** subtle glow `shadow-[0_0_24px_-8px_rgba(99,102,241,0.35)]`—do not stack multiple glows.
- **Shadows:** prefer **single** soft shadow; no heavy drop shadows on every card.

### C.5 Color usage rules

- **Backgrounds:** page `bg-zk-base`; grouped content `bg-zk-surface/30`–`bg-zk-elevated/50`; avoid pure black `#000`.
- **Primary CTA:** `bg-zk-indigo` → `hover:bg-zk-indigo-hover` + white text. **Do not** use legacy `bg-blue-600` on **new** work in files you touch.
- **Destructive:** keep a **single** destructive hue (existing reds are fine) but **tone down** saturation to fit zk-base (no fluorescent error reds).
- **Links (in prose):** `text-zk-cyan/90` hover `text-zk-cyan` **or** indigo underline pattern—pick **one** pattern per surface and stay consistent.
- **Do not** use `zk-cyan` for non-security decorative blobs (no random gradients).

### C.6 Motion

- **Allowed:** `opacity`, `translateY` max ~8–16px, `transition` 200–400ms, easing `cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1)` or `ease-out`.
- **Avoid:** bounce springs, spinners except loading states, scroll hijacking, parallax that shifts layout.
- Prefer **CSS transitions**; use **framer-motion** only where it already exists or for meaningful `whileInView` fades—do not add heavy motion deps to leaf components.

### C.7 Icons (`lucide-react`)

- Default stroke `strokeWidth={1.5}` on marketing-style surfaces; keep icons **small** (`h-4 w-4`–`h-5 w-5`) next to text.
- Icon color: `text-zk-muted` default; `text-zk-cyan` for security; `text-zk-safe` for encrypted/success; `text-zk-indigo` only when tied to primary action.

### C.8 Forms & inputs

- Inputs on dark: `bg-zk-base/80` or `bg-zk-elevated`, `border-zk-border`, `text-zk-text`, placeholder `placeholder:text-zk-muted/60`.
- Focus ring: `focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-zk-indigo/50 focus:ring-offset-2 focus:ring-offset-zk-base` (adjust offset to match surface).
- **Do not** change validation rules or `register()` field names—only styles and optional `aria-invalid` presentation.

### C.9 States: loading, empty, error

- **Loading:** subtle text `text-zk-muted` or thin progress; **no** playful copy unless product asks.
- **Empty:** one clear headline + one sentence + single CTA (`zk-indigo` button).
- **Error:** `text-red-400/90` on `bg-red-950/20` border `border-red-500/30`—keep contrast on `zk-base`.

### C.10 Toasts (`sonner`)

- Restyle via **wrapper** or global class if introduced later; until then, match surrounding page background so toasts do not look like legacy bright cards.

### C.11 Password app (`/pw`)

- May keep **distinct** accent (red theme) for product separation, but **shell** (nav if shared, typography, spacing) should still use `font-zk-sans` / ZK neutrals where PW-specific red is not the signal.
- Do not remove PW-specific guards (`PasswordAppGuard`, etc.).

### C.12 Public docs layout (`PublicLayout`, `PublicHeader`)

- Align `PublicHeader` / docs chrome with **MarketingNav** patterns (floating bar optional; at minimum shared colors and typography).
- **Do not** change doc markdown content unless editorial task.

