## Part D — Implementation conventions

- **Tailwind only** for layout/color in React files unless a file already uses CSS modules—do not introduce new styling systems.
- **Avoid** arbitrary `style={{}}` except one-off transforms already present.
- **Prefer** semantic HTML: `button` for actions, `a`/`Link` for navigation, headings in order.
- **Dark mode:** app is **dark-first**; do not add light theme unless explicitly requested.
- When removing old classes, **delete unused** imports (icons, components) in the same edit.

---

## Part E — Page-by-page rollout (suggested order)

1. **Global shell:** `Sidebar`, `MobileHeader`, `MobileNav`, `GlobalSearchBar`, `EncryptionStatusIndicator`
2. **Auth surfaces:** `LoginPage`, `ForgotPasswordPage`, `MasterPasswordModal` — layout/copy only; **no** changes to `AuthGuard` logic
3. **Core app:** `DashboardPage`, `ProjectDetailPage`, `CredentialsPage`, `ImportProjectPage`, `ProfilePage`
4. **Billing:** `PaywallPage`, `SubscriptionManagementPage`, billing return/canceled pages
5. **Files / modals:** `FileList`, `FileUploadArea`, `FilePreviewModal`, credential modals/cards
6. **Password app:** `LayoutShell`, toolbar, list, settings
7. **Docs:** `DocsPage`, `DocDetailPage`, `DocCard` to match public header refresh

Track completed areas in the PR description or a short checklist—**one mergeable vertical slice** (e.g. “sidebar + dashboard only”) is better than 40 files of half-updated colors.

---

## Part F — PR checklist (design-only PRs)

- [ ] No changes under `functions/`, `api/`, or Firestore rules unless ticket says so
- [ ] No changes to store **async** logic, HTTP/Firebase calls, or encryption code paths
- [ ] No new user-visible pricing/security claims without matching landing/pricing
- [ ] `npm run build` passes
- [ ] Keyboard: tab order unchanged or improved
- [ ] Touch targets ≥ ~44px for primary mobile actions

---

## Part G — When this rule conflicts with another instruction

If another rule or ticket says “change API behavior,” that instruction **wins** for that task. This rule is the **default** for **visual alignment** work.
